But if you're going to hone an edge or a model, you need to have a framework.

01:56:48.000 --> 01:56:50.000
And you start by back testing.

01:56:50.000 --> 01:57:01.000
In that back testing, in your annotations, you talk about how it feels good to see this move deliver as I was expecting from this fair value gap up to this buy-side liquidity pull during the hours of this and this.

01:57:01.000 --> 01:57:05.000
And this is what my model suggests I should be looking for each day.

01:57:05.000 --> 01:57:09.000
