01:57:09.000 --> 01:57:15.000
I was playing video games and I was watching some YouTube or talking about some nonsense and I missed the trade setup.

01:57:15.000 --> 01:57:16.000
I should have known better.

01:57:16.000 --> 01:57:17.000
Never do that kind of stuff.

01:57:17.000 --> 01:57:21.000
Not in your back testing, not in anything that you're recording in your journal.

01:57:21.000 --> 01:57:23.000
Everything has to be positive.

01:57:23.000 --> 01:57:27.000
You're sugarcoating everything in your back testing.

01:57:27.000 --> 01:57:32.000
You're tricking your brain to see that as experience.

01:57:32.000 --> 01:57:40.000
So that way when you see it forming live, you're not going to be in fear, in trepidation of, oh, it's going to be a painful experience.

01:57:40.000 --> 01:57:52.000
And again, when right now you don't have that experience yet, but because you keep logging in with back testing, you're filling your brain up with a lot of pseudo memories.

01:57:52.000 --> 01:58:00.000
So you're doing the ideal utilization of a lie.

01:58:00.000 --> 01:58:01.000
This is called what it is.

01:58:01.000 --> 01:58:06.000
You're lying to yourself, and trolls are going to love this.

01:58:06.000 --> 01:58:10.000
You're lying to yourself with positive reinforcement.

01:58:10.000 --> 01:58:22.000
So that way when you look at something forming in real time, it will be remembered and you won't have any negative triggering because of toxic annotations or toxic thinking.

01:58:22.000 --> 01:58:24.000
You'll have memories of, oh, yeah, I remember seeing that.

01:58:24.000 --> 01:58:28.000
And your subconscious, you may not see it or understand it or feel it when you're doing it.

01:58:28.000 --> 01:58:35.000
But your subconscious revert back to those experiences that you've logged with positive reinforcement.

